  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Majuli Island Community Based Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR)Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) HVCA implementation 

2) Establish ward level Disaster Management Committees (DMC) and Gram Panchayat (GP) level Task Force Teams (TFT) 

3) Household preparedness campaign implemented

4) Development of GP DRR plans &amp;amp; mainstreamed into GP development plans

5) Construction of pilot evacuation points 

6)Development of a sub division Disaster Management Plan (DMP) and review of District DMP 

7)District Early Warning System (EWS)established</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A Community Based DRR Project based in Majuli Island, Assam, India to increase resilience and reduce vulnerability of local community through improvement of disaster preparedness and response mechanisms, coupled with engagement with local authorities. Goal: To combine and link a bottom-up approach to household and community preparedness and mitigation with a top-down approach to strengthening DRR capacity at block, sub-division and district levels</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disaster vulnerable populations in 5 direct and 3 GPs</narrative>
  </description>
